===Etymology===
Compare French ''benjoin'', Spanish ''benjui'', Portuguese ''beijoin''; all from Arabic ''lub&#257;n-j&#257;w&#299;'' incense form Sumatra (named Java in Arabic), the first syllable being lost. Compare [[Benjamin]].

===Noun=== 
#A resinous substance, dry and brittle, obtained from the ''Styrax benzoin'', a tree of Sumatra, Java, etc., having a fragrant odor, and slightly aromatic taste. It is used in the preparation of benzoic acid, in medicine, and as a perfume.
#A white crystalline substance, C<sub>14</sub>H<sub>12</sub>O<sub>2</sub>, obtained from benzoic aldehyde and some other sources.
#''(Botany):'' The spicebush, ''Lindera benzoin''
